1583377124526< /Time>
<rating>5< /rating>< Review>
I highly recommend this place to anyone who's seeking superior customer service! I was in town for a quick trip and unfortunately landed a flat tire,  I was extremely concerned considering my tires usually have to be custom ordered since the majority of tire places don't carry this size tire on a daily basis, and my biggest concern was very few places have the machines to remove and replace the tire from the rim since the rim size is a 24". (They usually go up to a 20")
I called American Tire Depot around 10:00 am and spoke to Brett, I explained to him my situation in a panic and he handled the situation like a Boss. He made a quick call, ordered my tire and by 4pm had the tire there and ready to install,  not to mention he told me   that he checked and they did in fact have the proper machine to handle the 24" rim size.
When I arrived with my truck on a flat bed the guys in back had it in the garage in less then five minutes of it coming of the truck.  They were great as well,  everyone there had a positive and welcoming attitude,  they were professional,  efficent, and met all the specific accommodations needed to get the job done.
I was in and out of there in less then 45min to an hour.  Not only do they price match but already gave me the lowest price I've ever had on my tires.  I definitely give American Tire Depot as a business and the employees they have running the place a 5+ star rating.
Take any car year make or model there and you won't be disappointed.

<Rating>5<//Rating><review>I needed to get a few door dings and bumper repairs done on my Mazda car thanks to people "generously" hitting my car and not letting me know. I went by and spoke with Scott the owner. He seemed knowledgeable and gave me a great quote. He did the job as advertised and finished the day he promised. It was a fairly quick turn around. It only took 5 days for me to get it back. I definitely recommend him if you want great work at a fair price. It's never fun dealing with this type of chore but Scott made it as easy as possible.

My only remark to improve his service is in the details. He preferred me to pay via check but I needed to pay via credit card which he gets charged for (cost of doing business). I said I'd split the difference to help him out but this type of detail should be told up front to avoid the awkward discussion at the end. Also the rubbing compound used during the final buff was not completely removed. I went over my car afterwards with a fine tooth comb and had to buff off quite a bit of the rubbing compound in the little cracks, my emblems and down at the bottom of the car. I also found and peeled off a bunch of masking tape from under the car which was used to hold plastic to cover my car while he sprayed the parts he was repairing.

This all being said he did a good job. I did get a solid discount compared to some other quotes so I can't truly complain. I'm always a believer in you get what you pay for. So these minor details I can let slide but it would help the overall experience for his customers.<//review><pictures>None<//pictures>< response>

They have an outdoor patio but it was super hot to sit out. Needed some more shading outside. Dog friendly on the patio. They were nice enough to let us sit inside and our dog half outside. < Rating>
5</Rating>
<Text>We'd heard great things and we loved Ebullition's brewery, so we finally checked out Ebullition's gastropub. It exceeded all of our expectations. We started with the pretzel (which we'll get every time), Korean hot wings (perfect amount of heat), and the chef's new brussels sprouts with pork belly appetizer that our server recommended. I guess there's two appetizers we'll get every time. Amazing!

We paired this with the west coast style Dopamine double IPA and 65 and Sunny single IPA. Excellent hop-forward beers without overwhelming the palate.

For main dishes we enjoyed the burgers (another go-to) and both the seasoned fries and truffle fries (yum), the Reuben sandwich (watch out DZ Akins) and the crawfish chowder pie which was flaky, creamy and another surprise winner. The chef even came by the tables to inquire about our food. This place clearly cares about the quality of their beer and food.

With the main dishes we mixed it up with the Toucan Tart which was fruity and perfect on a warm evening. Our server suggested a neapolitan which is a blend of their Vanilla Porter and Strawberry Honey Pale Ale. This should be on the menu and we should have grabbed a crowler of this. Perfect beer to wrap up our first dinner at Ebullition Brew Works and Gastronomy.

Staff is friendly and knowledgeable, ambience is great, and the food is amazing.<//Text><pics>None< /pics>< Resp>

<username>Mike Doring< /username>< review>
Wanted to love this place as I live nearby, but I probably won't go back. Had a beer flight, 3 were below average, including one of the most boring hazy IPAs I've had, but the DIPA was decent. Service was very slow, but friendly. Seemed understaffed. Just had some snacks, which were OK, but can't really speak much to the food. Kind of cold on the patio as our heaters weren't working. So many great brewery options in the area, this one just doesn't stand out.<//review>

<Text>Last week, I was quoted a specific price on a Tacoma over email by Mark Shehadi in sales. I called to confirm and was put in touch with Keyth, the sales manager, who confirmed that was the price. I put a deposit on the truck and drove 3 hours up to the dealership the next day to sign the papers.

When Scott Abel (Finance manager) and I sat down to do financing, I was informed that they couldn't sell the truck to me at the quoted price and said they could only sell it for MSRP.  We went back and forth for a bit and clearly weren't on the same page, so I got up and drove the 3 hours back home empty-handed.

I don't think I've ever felt so screwed over, for lack of a better phrase. I took off work, drove all the way up there, and had a friend take off work so he could drive my other pickup back home.

Maybe there was a lack of communication and it was an honest mistake or maybe they thought I wouldn't leave without a truck no matter the price after driving 3 hours, but it cost myself and my friend a whole day of our time, not to mention the lost hours at both of our jobs.

I did two stars instead of 1 because Scott ended up sending me a small check for my inconvenience.  It doesn't come close to covering my lost hours at work and doesn't give me my day back, but at least he tried to make it somewhat right.

I will say that Monica and Jesse in sales were a pleasure to talk to while I waited to do paperwork. Too bad we couldn't do business but I ended up purchasing a very similar truck (minor differences in options) at a dealer much closer to home for around the price I was initially quoted at CardinaleWay.<//Text><pictures>None< /pictures><Response>None< /Response>< Gmap_id>

<name>Jen C</name><Time>1553125504929</Time><rate>5< /rate>< Text>
Excellent Work! I stopped by after checking raving reviews from various sites. I lucked out that the morning was free to take care of my car since I stopped by early. (It is usually appointment based as detailing does take time to do right.) Jose greeted me, and was very patient when I went over my situation.

Desperately needed my engine cleaned as I hadn't cleaned it in years, really embarrassed by how grimy it was. I also needed my headlight covers cleaned, they were frosted over completely and barely put out any light. I tried a hack solution that only worked for a little, and the dealership wanted to replace the entire headlight assembly unit for an insane amount. I had the interior cleaned a little as well.

Upon pick up, it was amazing! The engine was pristine and the headlight covers were sparkling. The next customer getting service was so impressed with the work, he wanted his light covers cleaned, too. (That night, I actually could see more than a couple feet in front of me with the regular beams on.) The interior was spick and span.

The customer service was immpecable. It is a family owned business. They are all nice and take much pride in their work. The price was extremely fair considering it was not easy for what needed to be done. Would definitely recommend. Thank you!<//Text>

<Review>I bring large groups of Japanese tourists to LAX and Disneyland several each year.  With my very large groups that insist on having toilets on a big bus, the more expensive, time limited, slower Disneyland Express wins out; but in my groups of a dozen or less (with no bathroom needs) Mickey‚Äôs totally dominates all other services. <date>1560789309251</date><Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
So, my mom booked a big Disneyland Express bus through AAA just as she had on trip 4 yrs ago. But, the bus didn't come (we saw it broken down on the side of the highway when we were leaving LAX. Mickey of Mickey's Space Ship Shuttle at first seemed sketchy with how he was trying to convince us to let him take us to our hotel. Ultimately, it was a good move because w/in an hour we arrived to our hotel near Katella & S Harbor Blvd by Disneyland. He could pack all 9 of us in, and our luggage, including 1 yr old. The van was really dated but had seat belts, a smooth ride, and we learned about local points along the way. The best part was that we were able to arrange for our return to LAX at the end of the week so we had a ride we could count on. The return bus w/Kelly was much newer. Same smooth ride, courteous driver & baby seat.  The big Disneyland Express bus we took 4 yrs ago was nicer looking & prettier. BUT, we will use & recommend the Mickey Space Ship Shuttle from now one. The Disneyland Express bus is harder to catch (run hourly &  hard to find @ LAX), no baby seats, can't navigate traffic as quickly, not local, poor communication. All things MSSS does better, even if the 1 van was old & well-used. For our group of 9, it was perfect. Despite my original hesitation, I fully recommend to any family. I was interested in the poor reviews and see how drivers tried to fill their busses to make it worth their while to drive. I recommend: determine prices, locations & payment types when trips are arranged. I think then things will all be fine.< /Text>

9/17/20

Roxie sandwiches are well made to how you want it.

Soooooo delicious!!!!!!!

Buy two, one for your girlfriend/boyfriend and switch halves.

Tony runs a happy crew and clean environment.

Who says that you can't eat a sandwich for dinner? Stop by Roxie's after work and get your jumbo sandwich, chips and drink....then settle back to watch your favorite movie, sports or tv program.

Relax and enjoy your Roxie sandwich.<//Review>

I heard about this place from my storage place. I figured why not, it's on my way home and I haven't had a really good classic sandwich in a long time. Upon arrival I knew this was going to be an awesome place just on the smell alone. A complete hole in the wall spot where everyone knows everyone. <text>I tumbled upon it and I was pleasantly surprised. They offer Roast Beef as a meat choice and it is pretty darn good. The sandwich is fairly thick, the ingredients taste fresh and they balance it well compared to the meat, the bread they use is good (I order Dutch crunch anytime I can) and the sandwich is properly toasted. They go for "Junior" for the smallest size, note that the "Regular" size is quite filling. It does get soggy pretty quickly due to the mayo/mustard so either you need to eat it right away or ask them to be light on those two.<//text>< pictures>

<text>Hand down, BEST Sandwiches in San Francisco! I'm so lucky to live in the Excelsior and have Roxie's just a hop, skip and jump away! My go to is a Regular Mortadella on Sourdough, everything on it, toasted. Some people think the bread to meat ratio is 60:40 but I think it's perfect. The guys that run the place are hilarious and never fail to make everyone feel welcome.

Although getting in line can be a bit confusing for people when they first come here, it's totally worth it. (For those who haven't tried Roxie's yet: When you come in the front door, walk along the drinks and sodas, and the line starts at the first deli case)

Keep up the great work, Roxie's</text>< Gmap_id>
